<p>HPE has created a series of small, simplified sample applications to help you understand and exercise the Development Platform services.</p>
<p>Each sample builds on the previous one and all source code is provided for you to build, deploy, and take apart. Each sample is provided in multiple languages.</p>
<section id="prerequisites-before-you-begin"> <title>Prerequisites - Before you begin</title>
<p>In order to download and deploy these sample applications, you must have the necessary framework installed and configured.</p>
<ul>
<li>HPE Helion <tm tmtype="reg">OpenStack</tm> <xref href="../../commercial/GA1/1.1.1commercial.helion-update.dita" >cloud deployed</xref>. Note that the Helion Development Platform version 1.2 will only run on HPE Helion OpenStack version 1.1.1.</li>
<li>Application Lifecycle Service <xref href="../../devplatform/1.2/1.2devplatform.deploy-ALS.dita" >Cluster</xref> available with MySQL and RabbitMQ enabled.
<ul>
<li>You can also quickly setup a cluster in the free and publicly available Helion cloud as part of the <xref href="1.2devplatform.ALS-developer-trial-quick-start.dita#topic1952" type="section"  >Quick Start Developer Trial</xref>: </li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Logon and password credentials for the cluster.</li>
<li>Access to the <xref href="../../devplatform/1.2/helion/user/client/1.2index.dita" >Helion command-line interface (CLI)</xref></li>
</ul>
</section>
